WorkItem.Description:
If a DataGridTextColumn cell has focus inside a data grid, regardless of whether it is in input mode or not, hitting an accelerator key will not cause the appropriate target control to get focus. Instead, focus will stay with the current data grid cell.
 
I was able to fix this by changing the source for DataGridTextColumn.OnInput from this
 
        internal override void OnInput(InputEventArgs e)
        {
            // Text input will start an edit
            if (e is TextCompositionEventArgs)
            {
                BeginEdit(e);    
            }
        }
 
to this
 
        internal override void OnInput(InputEventArgs e)
        {
            // Text input will start an edit
            if (e is TextCompositionEventArgs)
            {
                if (Keyboard.Modifiers == ModifierKeys.None || Keyboard.Modifiers == ModifierKeys.Shift)
                {
                    BeginEdit(e);    
                }
            }
        }
